deck: Hendorff is a security officer on the USS Enterprise
description: Hendorff is a security officer on the USS Enterprise. He kind of got off on a bad start with Captain Kirk who had insulted him at a bar by calling him Cupcake. They reconciled after Nero was defeated. Hendorff, of course, had found it difficult to handle Spock and McCoy. On one mission, Hendorff was attacked by a poisonous plant on the artificial planet Gamma Trianguli VI. Spock managed to keep Hendorff from being exposed to too many spines. While Hendorff's prime reality counterpart died under similar circumstances, Hendorff himself survived thanks to a blood transfusion from Spock which almost killed him. This was a first in medical history. Hendorff then told his parents all that happened. He said that he was proud of being a redshirt despite the reputation of redshirts being killed while on away missions.
name: Hendorff

description: Joseph Reese Latimer was the helmsman of the shuttlecraft Galileo for mission assigned by Captain Kirk of the Enterprise. The mission, led by the First Officer Commander Spock, was to explore Murasaki 312, an unusual space anomaly. When the shuttlecraft entered the anomaly, the energy sent it to Taurus II. While exploring Taurus II, Latimer was killed by one of the natives using a spear that bared a resemblance to a Folsom Point from prehistoric North America as Spock noticed.
name: Joseph Latimer

description: Samuel Boma was a crewmember of the Enterprise who was assigned by Captain Kirk on a mission to Murasaki 312. When the shuttlecraft Galileo was diverted to Taurus II, Mr. Boma was shaken up. He got mad after Latimer was killed when Spock noticed a Folsom point and commented on it. Spock was in charge and used logic because he was half-Vulcan. When Boma or any of the other Human crewmembers wanted to attack the natives of Taurus II, Spock would not let them.Eventually, Samuel Boma had had enough started arguing a lot with Spock. He later apologized just before the survivors of the Galileo Seven, including Boma and Spock, returned to the Enterprise.
name: Samuel Boma

description: Mitchell Ferris was the Federation High Commissioner who was assigned to the Enterprise to oversee the delivery of vaccines to Makus III in time for their delivery to New Paris which was going through an epidemic. He was impatient and thus was not happy when Captain Kirk to stop at Murasaki 312 on the way. When seven crewmembers ended up on Taurus II, the Enterprise followed to see if they could attempt a rescue. Mitchell Ferris gave Captain Kirk a time limit within which to rescue the Galileo Seven, led by Spock. When that time limit expired, the Enterprise started to leave but not before rescuing the survivors of the Galileo Seven.
name: Mitchell Ferris

description: Science Officer 0718 is an artificial lifeform created by the USS Enterprise just a little while before the events of Star Trek Into Darkness. He was originally an avatar of the Enterprise's computer. However, after that computer returned to its mainframe to save the crew, the body that was left was revived by Spock and became part of the crew of the Enterprise with no memory of previous events. He did not have a name, but instead used his Starfleet ID number, 0718. In the years that followed, Science Officer 0718 became known as the first and only humanoid-machine interface in Starfleet whose job on the Enterprise was to run diagnostics to make sure the Enterprise was okay as seen Star Trek Into Darkness. He also became known as a scientist who spent time in the botanical lab during his spare time. He has been working on a paper comparing the biological nervous system and the circuitry of a computer.
name: Science Officer 0718

deck: Raga is an evil sentient planet, the brother of Mogo, who wanted to spread himself across the universe.
description:
Origin

Raga is a sentient planet. Raga and his siblings yearned to have life on their surface and they each searched out inhabitants. But soon they learned that smaller life only took and killed themselves, destroying and scaring. Raga fought back by killing all his inhabitants, and these action cause one of his brothers to kill him.

Creation

Raga was created by writer Justin Jordan and artist Diogenes Neves and first appeared in Green Lantern: New Guardians #31.

Major Story Arcs

Dead World

For more information see: Green Lantern: New Guardians #31

Kyle Rayner finds himself on a dead world, and wanders toward a city in the distance. There he finds signs that life used to be plentiful on the now dead planet. He soon realizes he is being followed by some sort of life, and comes to the conclusion he is on a dead version of Mogo. He then flies to the "Heart of a Living Planet" and uses his White Power Ring to give the heart a spark of life.

This makes Raga less dead, and he communicates with Kyle, he tells of how he and his sibling yearns to witness life and this was his siblings down fall, but not Raga nor his brother Mogo. Raga kills all life on his surface and causes Mogo to kill Raga.

But now Kyle gave him his spark of life again and now Raga is going to spread across the universe and kill all life. Upon learning this Kyle destroys the spark of life making Raga completely dead once again.
name: Raga
